                <kp-step-abstract>Standard Java applications can run without modification
                    in a real-time JVM to achieve real-time goals. The Metronome garbage
                    collector and Ahead-of-time (AOT) compilation—two key features in IBM
                    WebSphere Real Time—let your real-time applications retain the
                    benefits of Java portability. Understand how these features help turn
